Class LineNumberTableReader

java.lang.Object
com.ibm.wala.shrike.shrikeCT.AttributeReader
com.ibm.wala.shrike.shrikeCT.LineNumberTableReader
public final class LineNumberTableReader extends AttributeReader
This class reads LineNumberTable attributes.

Instead of constructing a LineNumberTableReader directly, consider just calling LineNumberTableReader.makeBytecodeToSourceMap for convenient access to aggregate line number data from all the LineNumberTable attributes for a given Code.

    • makeBytecodeToSourceMap

      public static int[] makeBytecodeToSourceMap(CodeReader code) throws InvalidClassFileException, IllegalArgumentException
      Construct a "bytecode to source" map for the given code. This method aggregates all the LineNumberTable attributes for the code into one handy data structure.
      Returns:
      an array mapping each byte of the bytecode bytes to the line number that that byte belongs to, or null if there is no line number data in the Code
      Throws:
      InvalidClassFileException
      IllegalArgumentException
